{"questionId":"22208455","questionHtml":"<p>By using part (a) or otherwise, show that the Maclaurin series for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;up to and including the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math> term is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mn>0</mn></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mn>0</mn></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>f</mi><mo>''</mo><mfenced><mn>0</mn></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>''</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced><mo>!</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced><mo>!</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>